nel)|Alibi]])\n* ''[[Rosemary & Thyme]]'' (now on [[Drama (UK TV channel)|Drama]])\n* ''[[Rumpole of the Bailey]]'' (now on [[Drama (UK TV channel)|Drama]])\n* ''[[Sherlock Holmes (1984 TV series)|Sherlock Holmes]]'' (now on [[ITV4]])\n* ''[[Taggart]]'' (now on [[Drama (UK TV channel)|Drama]])\n* ''[[Tales of the Unexpected (TV series)|Tales of the Unexpected]]'' (now on [[Sky Arts]])\n* ''[[The Two Ronnies]]'' (now on [[Gold (UK TV channel)|Gold]])\n* ''[[Trial and Retribution]]'' (now on [[Drama (UK TV channel)|Drama]])\n* ''[[The Vice (TV series)|The Vice]]''\n* ''[[Where the Heart Is (British TV series)|Where the Heart Is]]'' (now on [[Drama (UK TV channel)|Drama]])\n* ''[[Who Wants to Be a Millionaire?]]'' (now on [[Challenge (TV channel)|Challenge]])\n* ''[[Wycliffe (TV series)|Wycliffe]]'' (now on [[Drama (UK TV channel)|Drama]])\n\n==Most watched programmes==\nThe following is a list of the ten most watched broadcasts on ITV3 since launch, based on Live +7 data supplied by [[BARB]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.barb.co.uk/viewing-data/weekly-top-10/ |title=Weekly Top 10 Programmes |publisher=Barb.co.uk |date=23 October 2017}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Rank !! Programme!! Number of Viewers !! Date\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1 || ''[[Foyle's War]]'' || 1,710,000 || 23 March 2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2 || rowspan=\"2\" | ''[[Lewis (TV series)|Lewis]]'' || 1,504,000 || 14 July 2012\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|3 || 1,486,000 || 16 July 2012\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|4 || rowspan=\"2\" | ''Foyle's War'' || 1,473,000 || 14 January 2012\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|5 || 1,467,000 || 21 January 2012\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|6 || ''Lewis'' || 1,429,000 || 1 July 2012\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|7 || rowspan=\"2\" | ''[[Midsomer Murders]] '' || 1,425,000 || 4 July 2014\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|8 || 1,414,000 || 8 January 2011\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|9 || rowspan=\"2\"