 data (when known) -->\n| owner = <!-- or: | owners = -->\n| members = \n| members_year = <!-- Year of members data (when known) -->\n| num_employees = \n| num_employees_year = <!-- Year of num_employees data (when known) -->\n| parent = \n| divisions = \n| subsid = \n| module = <!-- Used to embed other templates -->\n| website = {{url|https://www.poptelecom.co.uk}} <!-- or: | homepage = --><!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| footnotes = \n}}\n\n'''POP Telecom''' is a [[UK]] based telecommunications and internet service provider (ISP) founded in 2011<ref>https://www.poptelecom.co.uk/index.php?/page/about-us</ref>, with headquarters based in Romford and is one of the largest fixed line, broadband and mobile networks in the UK. POP Telecom supply both line, broadband and mobile services to both domestic and commercial markets. POP Telecom\u2019s motto is \u201csimply communicating by communicating simply\u201d. POP Telecom are currently planning to expand on a multinational level.\n\nIn 2013, The POP Group was launched with an expansion in to the Business Energy Sector. POP Energy continues growing exponentially in the online and outbound world, with their goals prioritised in saving money on utility bills.\n\n== Services ==\nPOP telecom currently provides standard ADSL broadband, VDSL Fibre broadband, IP Stream rural broadband, VOIP services and line for residential and business customers. \nPOP telecom is especially well known for having a UK based customer service with sales, relations, technical support and billing departments.\n\nSubject to availability, POP telecom also offers all-inclusive customised deals and packages for families, over 60\u2019s students, landlords and gamers. \nPOP telecom services can be ordered both by phone, through the online website or through partnering stores such as Currys/PC world, Carphone warehouse and Hughes Electrical.\n\n== Network ==\nPOP Telecom believes that everyone should have access to broadband services, currently their network covers 94% of the United Kingdom for home and business customers and are still expanding. \nPOP Telecom also operates a mobile service using primarily using the EE and Vodafone 4G networks as a mobile virtual network operator.\n\nPOP Mobile offers business contracts and consumer deals that cover 98% of the UK population and expanding. The uptime for POP telecom is said to be up to 99.9% with UK based customer service to assist with technical and non-technical issues.\n\nThe POP Telecom network includes\n\n* 2,600+ unbundled broadband exchanges.\n* 2,198 EFM exchanges\n* 1,943 on net Fibre exchanges\n* Over 5,000 exchanges capable of taking Fibre\n* 1,100 Superfast Broadband exchanges\n* 30,000 cabinets ready for Superfast Broadband\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n* [http://www.thisismoney.co.uk/money/bills/article-2663577/Pop-Telecom-beats-competition-launch-new-low-cost-broadband-deal.html The broadband that costs just \u00a31 a month]<br />\n* [http://www.mobiletoday.co.uk/news/b2b/31388/pop-telecom-to-launch-major-assault-on-b2b-market-.aspx Pop Telecom to launch major assault on b2b market]\n\n== External links ==\n{{Official website|poptelecom.co.uk}}\n\n[[Category:1988 establishments in England]]\n[[Category:Companies established in 1988]]\n[[Category:Romford]]\n[[Category:Telecommunications companies of the United Kingdom]]\n\n\n{{UK-company-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{no footnotes|date=March 2015}}\n{{more citations needed|date=March 2015}}\n{{Orphan|date=August 2015}}\n}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = POP Telecom\n| logo = [https://www.poptelecom.co.uk/assets/img/logo.png]\n| logo_size = \n| logo_alt = Poptelecom Logo\n| logo_caption = Poptelecom Logo\n| logo_padding = \n| image = \n| image_size = \n| image_alt = \n| image_caption = \n| trading_name = \n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = <!-- Use ISO 639-1 code, e.g. \"fr\" for French. For multiple names in different languages, use {{lang|[code]|[name]}}. -->\n| romanized_name = \